The 2019 MyBroadband Fibre Conference will take place on Wednesday 17 July at The Venue in Houghton and has attracted top industry experts as speakers. The conference will focus on fibre networks and services in South Africa, with topics ranging from network roll-outs and FTTx technologies to ISP services and 5G. Radio 702’s Aki Anastasiou will serve as emcee for the event and will be joined by SEACOM Chief Strategy Officer Suveer Ramdhani and Octotel CEO Rob Gilmour. Other speakers include DFA executive Vino Govender, CipherWave MD Wayne D’SA and MTN head of enterprise planning and solution architecture Calvin Govender. Tickets for the 2019 Fibre Conference are still available at a discount using the promotional code below. Many top fibre companies have partnered with MyBroadband for the 2019 Fibre Conference, including DFA, Dartcom, Broadband Infraco, MetroFibre, MiRO and Angola Cables. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-312469" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Sponsors.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="774" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Sponsors.jpg 690w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Sponsors-331x400.jpg 331w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Sponsors-355x430.jpg 355w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />